question.comments: Clique Changes in the matrix format in combination with animation were practically impossible. Animation made it harder to count degrees/clique size overall. I found Node Link in combination with the Timeline to be the most readable format, since you could already zoom in to the nodes that concerned you and then jump between the different times easily, without losing focus. Juxtaposition worked best in Matrix Format, since the resulting thick lines in the node link format overlapped often and covered each other up, which made it easy to overlook a single connection.
